        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-08-22T18:03:00.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"172948\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"172948\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>For me, those are Denis\u2019 two best ever wines! With 1999 having the edge. Both are drinking very well now, but I\u2019d probably pick the 1999. I wouldn\u2019t double or single decant, the wine doesn\u2019t need it.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I have the 1993 too but it isn\u2019t up.</p>\n<p>I will double decant if for no reason other than to protect from sediment en route to and in the restaurant.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Fair enough! In that case, the 2002 is just a touch more primary and you might loose less/gain more in the decanting.</p>",
