        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/d78d45/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-08-22T19:08:30.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"172948\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Great idea.</p>\n<p>What makes sense out of what I have would be 1999 Mugnier Fu\u00e9es, 1999 Cathiard Murgers, 2002 Bachelet Corbeaux, or 2005 Mugnier Mar\u00e9chale.</p>\n<p>My parents are coming over for dinner tonight. I think they would have really enjoyed Becky and definitely thought Russel to be a hoot.</p>\n<p>Oh, and the 1999 Bachelet Charmes is the best wine I ever had from Bachelet. Not that I\u2019ve had as many different wines and vintages as true enthusiasts.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Well. Save the 1999 Mugnier for me. I can pair it with the 01 or 02.</p>\n<p>I would try either the Cathiard or the Bachelet.</p>",
