      {
        "id": 3221512,
        "name": "Tom Blach",
        "username": "Tom_Blach",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/9dc877/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2021-08-22T19:41:46.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"172948\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Four of us are dining out tonight and bringing \u201cBecky\u201d wines to celebrate her life. I am trying to choose between 2002 and 1999 Bachelet Charmes-Chambertin, bith owned by me since release. I\u2019ve not had the 02 and actually stood it up a few weeks ago to try sometime soon. The 1999 I have had several times (but not since five years ago, when I found it relatively shut down but also only opened shortly before drinking in a restaurant) but stood up only a couple of days ago. Which would you choose and how much in advance would you double decant?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>A recent pairing of the Corbeaux of those vintages was a real eye-opener; I\u2019ve not always been convinced that the Corbeaux was a better wine than the superb village VV but the 99 at least was absolutely sensational, almost at the level of the Charmes.</p>\n<p>Yesterday I bought a case of Nicolas Perrault Maranges Clos Des Loyeres 2018 in tribute.</p>",
